import { createActions } from 'redux-actions';

export const {
  login,
  loginSuccess,
  authorizationError,
  logout,
  logoutSuccess,
  registration,
  resetUserReducer,
  setLang,
  authorizationLoading,
  getUserData,
  getUserDataLoading,
  getUserDataSuccess,
  getUserDataError,
} = createActions(
  'LOGIN',
  'LOGIN_SUCCESS',
  'AUTHORIZATION_ERROR',
  'RESET_USER_REDUCER',
  'LOGOUT',
  'LOGOUT_SUCCESS',
  'REGISTRATION',
  'SET_LANG',
  'AUTHORIZATION_LOADING',
  'GET_USER_DATA',
  'GET_USER_DATA_LOADING',
  'GET_USER_DATA_SUCCESS',
  'GET_USER_DATA_ERROR',
);
